  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until it is translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, cummin seeds, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until it is browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chickpea flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chicken broth and yeast, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Remove the pot from the heat and let it cool slightly.",
    "Serve the seco de cordero hot, garnished with chopped fresh cilantro if desired."
